There are two kinds of calyx. One is Caly!- like arum, and grows on ploughed land. It is gathered before it withers, and has the sanie uses as aris. Its root is also taken in drink as a powerful aperient and emmenagogue, while its stallis, boiled down with the leaves in pulse‚ cures tenesmus. XXXVII. The other kind of it is called by some anchusa, by others rhinoclia, having leaves like those of lettuce, but longer and downy, and a red root. This applied with the finest pearl barley cures erysipelas, and, taken in white wine, liver complaints. XXXVIII.
